<a name="interests">
<h2> Research Interests </h2>
<ul>
<li> Complexity theory </li>
<li> Logic, bounded arithmetic
<li> propositional theorem proving (both lower bounds as well as
automated theorem proving
<li> concrete complexity theory, algorithms
</ul>

<a name="pubs">
<h2> Recent Papers </h2>
<ul>
<li><!WA1><a href="http://www.cs.arizona.edu/people/toni/papers/bceip-stoc95.ps"> The relative complexity of NP
        Search Problems</a>, with Paul Beame, Steve Cook, Jeff Edmonds and
        Russell Impagliazzo.
        <i> Proceedings from 27th ACM Symposium on Theory of Computing</i>,
        1995, pp. 303-314.

<li><!WA2><a href="http://www.cs.arizona.edu/people/toni/papers/bonet-pitassi-raz.ps"> Lower bounds for Cutting
        Planes proofs with Small Coefficients</a>, with Maria Bonet
        and Ran Raz.
        <i> Proceedings from 26th ACM Symposium on Theory of Computing</i>,
        1995, pp. 575-584. (The full version of this paper will appear
        in the Journal of Symbolic Logic.) 
       
<li><!WA3><a href="http://www.cs.arizona.edu/people/toni/papers/buss-pitassi-induction.ps"> Good degree bounds
        on Nullstellensatz refutations of the induction principle</a>,
        with Sam Buss.
        <i> Proceedings from the Symposium on Computational 
        Complexity, 1996</i>.

<li><!WA4><a href="http://www.cs.arizona.edu/people/toni/papers/hajos.ps"> The complexity of the Hajos Calculus</a>,
	with Alasdair Urquhart.
	<i>Proceedings from 33rd IEEE Symposium on Foundations of Computer
        Science</i>, pp. 187-196. (The full version of this paper 
        appeared in SIAM Journal on Discrete Mathematics, Vol 8, Issue 3,
        August 1995.)

<li><!WA5><a href="http://www.cs.arizona.edu/people/toni/papers/nullsatz-focs94.ps"> Lower bounds for Hilbert's 
        Nullstellensatz and propositional proofs</a>,
        with Paul Beame, Russell Impagliazzo, Jan Krajicek and Pavel Pudlak.
	<i>Proceedings from 35th IEEE Symposium on Foundations of
        Computer Science</i>, 1994, pp. 794-806.
